    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n(This is a \"work plan\" for https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/22313 )\n\nhttps://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter should be upstreamed in a form similar to [nvim-lspconfig](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig), using the power of magic 🌈 \n\nKnown issues:\n\n- queries may be editor specific (nvim vs helix vs ...)\n- parsers don't always maintain their own queries\n- supply-chain attacks (malicious parsers)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nUsers can easily install the \"top 20\" treesitter parsers with a single `vim.pack.add{}` call. (Note: Nvim already ships 5 builtin parsers.)\n\n- Provide a ~~`neovim/nvim-tsconfig`~~ `neovim/nvim-treeconfig` repo which has a similar role as `neovim/nvim-lspconfig`.\n    - It is \"data-only\", it doesn't have a \"framework\". No \"indent\" support. (Features requiring a framework should live in Nvim's own stdlib.)\n    - Limited scope, only support the \"top N\" parsers. (Can reconsider this if/when we find a sustainble maintenance model.)\n    - Parser-related shit (including queries) is owned by the parsers.\n- See sub-issues.\n\n### Reference\n\nOther nvim-treesitter alternatives:\n\n- https://github.com/lewis6991/ts-install.nvim\n- https://github.com/arborist-ts/arborist.nvim\n- https://github.com/romus204/tree-sitter-manager.nvim",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@justinmk Just a thought on the name `nvim-tsconfig`: \"tsconfig\" is very likely going to get confused with [TypeScript's tsconfig.json](https://www.typescriptlang.org/tsconfig/).\n\nWhile it's not as consistent with the naming of nvim-lspconfig, I would like to suggest the name \"treesitter-config.nvim\". Thoughts?",
