            "body": "It's really not a big deal, because \"ts\" in the context of *Nvim core concepts* never means \"typescript\". \n\nAnyway no point in debating, this is all vaporware currently.\n\n> I would like to suggest the name \"treesitter-config.nvim\".\n\nThat is randomly different than the `nvim-lspconfig` naming convention which was chosen quite carefully. \n\n~~We probably should just name it... `nvim-treesitter`.~~ No, that's too confusing.",
