            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Any plans for a binary only distribution method? Or perhaps build in a container if podman or docker are in path? I don't think it is at all reasonable one needs to have a full C build toolchain available to add TS parsers to enable decent highlighting for languages neovim has _chosen_ to not ship support for. Not all of us partook in nvim-treesitter but a simple copypasta from X to Y seems like discarding the baby and the bathwater (understood that isn't entirely what is stated here but I am reading between the lines).\n\nNote: Nvim already shipping 5 builtin parsers isn't enough. Why not ship 50+? Other editors include support for highlighting dozens of languages ootb. Why do we still need yet another plugin to achieve basic usability?",
